<p>Unfortunately, there are a few bad guys out there that you need to be aware of on the trail. The most common one is Devil's Club. It's easy to spot as it looks like a shrub with over-sized maple leaves. The problem with this shrub is the underside of the leaf which contains tiny prickles. These prickles can cause severe inflammation when contact with the skin occurs.</p>

